We're not the only ones who feels the loss of our Oshie. Gordie Girl misses her brother too. She spends most days laying on the floor, not wanting to do anything. She's been sad and not acting like her usual self. She's not the same puppy she was almost two weeks ago. 

Today was the first time I saw her somewhat happy since we came home without our boy. She ran around outside with neighborhood kids and played until she was tired. 🩷

Jesse and I have been loving on Gordie extra these past couple days. We've made a promise to both her and Oshie that we'll give her the best life possible and to always cherish every moment.
We were hiding from Gordie and Sophia 😅 We both needed a break lol

Our sweet Oshie crossed the rainbow bridge on Friday, 13 October 2023, after going into respiratory distress while on our way to Oceanside, CA.

We rented a pet friendly beach cottage on Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton from 13-16 October to spend a few days with Oshie & Gordie on the beach. But we never even made it into the water with him. 

He panted pretty heavily for about 5 hours straight. By the time we got him to an Urgent Care, it was too late. The Vet said his temperature was 107°F when we arrived. It went up to 108° and then she got him down to 104°. She told us to prepare ourselves for potential brain damage and organ failure caused by his temperature. I told her to do every test and everything she possibly could.

After doing everything she possibly could, she let all of us in the back room to see him. As soon as we walked in and saw Oshie laying on the table, I knew. I felt this incredible pain in my chest and knot in my throat that I've never felt before. I knelt down in front of him and said, "I'm so sorry, Oshie Boy. Mama is here." I saw his eyes move to look at me. But that was the only reaction we got from him. We all said our goodbyes. Including Gordie. 

I laid my head on Oshie and rubbed his belly and his side while the medication was administered, and then he was gone. Just like that. My Oshie Boy, the sweetest, most beautiful boy I've ever known, was gone. He didn't deserve to go like this. 

Jesse and I still feel an immense amount of guilt. We should have brought him in sooner that day or never traveled. We just thought he was panting loudly like he always did. Every video I have of him shows him panting loudly. But, he always calmed down after a while. Not this time, though. We just never thought his panting combined with excitement would lead to his passing. 

The Urgent Care Vet said he sounded like a dog with Laryngeal Paralysis when we first arrived. His regular Vet had told us 5 weeks earlier that she too believed he may have had Laryngeal Paralysis as-well. But, he was never officially diagnosed. His appointment with an Internal Medicine Specialist was scheduled for 19 October. We never made it.
I love you more than you could know. Please don't go.

Emily, Madison, Alena, John John, Audrey, Alex & Adelyn, Oshie loved you guys!❤️ I'm also very thankful that Oshie was able to spend a year and a half being the best big brother to his human sister. Sophia loves all animals because of you, Oshie.
Halloween 2017 with my favorite lion 🦁
Halloween 2023. Family pics felt different this year without Oshie.
Our trip to Tahoe a couple years ago was so much fun! Oshie played in the snow and hiked to the top of mountains overlooking the lake. He will always be my favorite view though 🥰
If Oshie and Gordie were in a PIXAR movie..They'd probably look something like this 🥰
Joy. Oshie was pure Joy ❤️ He loved the beach (and his mama) and always smiled. He was the friendliest, most gentle boy. We miss you so much Oshie.

Footage from Nov 7, 2021. This was the last trip to the beach with Oshie and Gordie before we moved from Monterey, CA to 29 Palms. On Oct 13, 2023, we were headed to the beach with Oshie and Gordie once again, but our boy never made it. The beach was his favorite place, and it saddens me he never made it in the water 💔
I miss the joy you brought into our lives. I miss you every moment of every day, Oshie. 💔

Happy 248th Birthday to the greatest fighting organization in the world. Oshie spent a lot of time around the Marines ❤️
Semper Fidelis !
Oshie was a quick learner. I had an "I love you" button for him, which he used whenever he wanted something me haha. He knew I'd give him anything if he told me he loved me 🩷

A couple of years ago, our friend Fabrizia @lucylu_art_  made a portrait of our Oshie Boy. This Portrait now hangs in our living room above Oshie's Urn. She captured his personality so well, and I'm thankful we found her! If you haven't already, please follow her and admire her amazing artwork.
Oshie wasn't the biggest fan of Gordie when we first brought her home. Over time, though, Gordie won him over. He was her best friend and misses him as much as we do.
Oshie did a great job teaching Gordie when she first came home. He was such a good big brother despite having to share his toys with a new sibling.

Oshie Boy Forever in our hearts 🩷
#petloss

I had Oshie's pawprint tattooed on my ribs in 2019. Last night, @smileyartla added my favorite picture of Oshie on my leg. 
Thank you, Smiley!! 
The picture of Oshie was taken during our trip to Yosemite in 2020. Oshie hiked miles and miles of trails, swam in rivers, and rolled around in the snow. He was so happy there, and I'm thankful we were able to explore such a beautiful place with the most beautiful boy 🥰 #petloss #petgrief #tattoos #dogportrait #dogportraittattoo #goldenretrievers

When I get to Heaven, the first thing I'm going to do is find you. The second thing I'll do is never let you go again. So much has changed since you've been away. You were family, Oshie. Losing you hurts so much, I can't breathe. I feel like those closest to me have forgotten you, but I never will. My heart never will. I don't feel like celebrating any holiday because I want to share them with you like I did the last 9 years. I miss you so much. 
#petloss #petgrief

We met Tim and Lisa and their beautiful Goldens Coop & Willow @cooper_and_willow_adventures via Social Media when we lived in Fallbrook in 2017/2018. This short clip is from the time we stayed in their home on our way back from our trip to Lake Tahoe in 2020. Oshie and Cooper were looking for the bacon, and of course, I shared a piece with them haha. I mean, look at those beautiful faces. They were starving! Poor puppies 😄

Social Media has allowed us to meet amazing people throughout these years, but Tim and Lisa have become family. I want to thank them for their friendship all these years and for loving my Oshie Boy. 🩷

They have traveled long distances to attend Oshie's previous Birthday parties and to meet Gordie when we first brought her home. We can't thank them enough for how much we truly appreciate them being in our lives. We miss you guys!
Correction: Mama needed a break from the screaming, not even 2 year old, yet 😂.

I'll never forget the first time Oshie met Santa. He was so excited! I miss his face, his smile, and his energy. He had such a kind and gentle soul. He was pure joy. This will be the first Christmas in 9 years without him, and I just don't feel like celebrating, but I'm going through the motions so that Sophia can enjoy the holiday. Life isn't fair sometimes. All I want is my boy back. 
#petloss #petgrief #goldenretrievers

Oshie was such an important part of our story. He helped write it. I miss his smile and his big, beautiful brown eyes that looked right into your soul when you talked to him. He was good. He was gentle, loving, and a happy boy. He brought so much joy into our lives. Losing him has been the most painful event of my life.
#petloss #petgrief

He was the perfect boy. Santa would have loved him ❤️
#petgrief #petloss

2 months without my Oshie and time does not make it any easier. 9 years wasn't enough time. 💔

Merry Christmas! ☃️🎄
